																	</h4>
								<div class="postinfo">
									Posted on 2009-02-27@01:52
																																			</div>
																Sorry Bryan and Anonymous. XRandR has no notion of "primary" or "secondary" monitors. All monitors are equal. They appear whatever order the driver detects them which is entirely arbitrary and desktop environments shouldn't care what order they are in.<br />
<br />
If you're using Gnome then you can simply drag your toolbars and panels to the other monitor and be done with it.
							</div>
