																	</h4>
								<div class="postinfo">
									Posted on 2009-03-15@20:32
																																			</div>
																#1 This is perfect.  For the past couple of days I've been customizing Xubuntu for my 2,1 MacBook, and this is the best solution so far for my external monitor.  In my case I had to make some mod's; perhaps the default scripting language is not [precisely] the same as Debian's.<br />
Here's how my "45custom_xrandr" looks now:<br />
	xrandr | grep "TMDS-1   connected"<br />
	if [ $? != 0 ]; then<br />
	   xrandr --output LVDS --mode 1280x800 --pos 0x26 --output TMDS-1 --mode 1920x1200 --pos 1280x0<br />
	   if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then<br />
	      xrandr --output LVDS --mode auto --output TMDS-1 --off<br />
	   fi<br />
	#debug   echo "'if [ 1 != 0 ]; then' worked"<br />
	else<br />
	   xrandr --output LVDS --mode 1280x800 --output TMDS-1 --off<br />
	#debug   echo "'if [ 1 != 0 ]; then' did not work"<br />
	fi<br />
<br />
#2 .. Looking forward to implementing the close-lid-script ...<br />
<br />
#3 And yes, grandr rocks too.
