																It sounds like your laptop monitor isn't really off, but mirrorring your laptop screen. Are you sure that your laptop screen is referred to as LVDS? It's different per driver.<br />
<br />
You also need to make sure that your desktop isn't overriding youd XRandR settings again. Gnome 2.x did that. I don't know if Gnome 3 or KDE 4 do something similar.
